  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Postoperative delirium is a common and important complication in patients. The aim of this
      study was to investigate whether preoperative anxiety predicted onset of postoperative
      delirium in elderly patients undergoing orthopaedic surgery, so as to help develop preventive
      approaches.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
